what is css?
CSS means cascading style sheets , it adds styles to the web page.
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
How does CSS work under the hood?
The browser converts HTML CSS into DOM. DOM represents the document in the computer memory.
It combines the documents content with its style.Browser then displays the contents of the DOM.

Load HTML ----> Parse HTML---->Create DOM True -----> Display
                     |                                    |
                  Loads CSS---->Parse CSS------------------>   
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
Differeny ways of using css in an application /?

Inline
Adding the style in the element itself using style attribute.
example :

<div style="width:200px;height:100px"></div>

Internal
Adding the CSS styles in style tag under header.
<head>
  <style>
    .app{
      width:100px;
      height:200px;
    }
  </styel>
</head>

External
write ur css in a separate file and add it to ur HTML page using the link tag.
Example : <link rel="url/styles.css"></link>
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
What are CSS selectors :

id selector
class selector
element selector
attribute selector
* - universal selector - to select all elements.
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
What is diff between class selectors and id selectors?
Class selectors can be reused whereas id selectors are for single elements. 

class selector- represented by a .
id - rep by #

example : 

  .app{
    width:50px;
  }
  
   #appOne{
    width:50px;
  }
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
What is box model?
Box model describes visual formatting for an element. 
It has properties like :
1.Padding
2.Border
3.Margins
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
What is responsive web design?
This technique is used to display the web page perfectly on every screen size and device.
We dont have to create different web pages for each device.

Example: mobile,desktop, laptop, tablets.
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
What are media queries ?
They are used for RWD.It applies different styles for diff devices.
Example: @media only screen and (max width: 600px){
//css styles
}
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
What are css positions ?

This specifies the type of positioning method used for an element.
There are totally 5 positions.
Position: fixed;
Position: static;
Position: absolute;
Position: sticky;
Position: relative;

Elements are then positioned using top, bottom, left and right properties.
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
What are css spirits?
CSS spirits are used to reduce the loading time for a web page because it combines various small images into one image.
It reduces no. of Http requests and hence the loading time.
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
What is reset or normalize CSS?
To have a generic default CSS property values we use this.To override the default settings 
of the browser and to have same default values. 
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
How do u hide an element using css?
option1
 visibility : hidden
 
option2 
 display:none
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
What is the difference between visibility : hidden and display:none ?
visibility:hidden elements take up the space on page whereas display:none wont take up space on page.
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
What is Z index?
It helps elements to overlap one-another and element with higher Z index is stacked above than a lower-index
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
What are pseudo classes?
pseudo class is used to define a special state of an element.

example:
 style an element when it gets focused.
 pseudo class is represented using :
 
 div:hover{
 background-color:blue;
 }
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
What are pseudo elements?
pseudo element is used to style specified parts of an element.

example :

style the first letter /orline of an element.

p::first-line {
color : #ff00000;
}
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
What are different units used in CSS?
there are two categories relative length and absolute length. 

example of absolute length : px (pixel)
example of relative length : em ()
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
What is the overflow property in css used for ?
It delas with the content overflow and element box. (content is too big to fit in a specified area.)
example: overflow scroll;
         overflow none;
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
What is !importance ?  
It overwrites all previous styling rules.

element {
  color : blue !importance;
}
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
What is css flex box?
flexible box layout model. It is a new layout model in CSS3. It places the elements dynamically based on 
the available properties. It has ability to modify the child elements to fill the available space in 
different screen sizes.
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
What are css pre-processors?
Its a program that lets u generate from preprocessors own unique syntax.
example: nested selector.

example of pre-processors:
SASS, LESS
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
What are vendor-prefixes?
To support the few styles in different browsers we use this vendor prefixes for styles.
example :
 -webkit- used for Chrome,safari.
 -moz-  Firefox
 -ms-  Internet Explorer and Microsoft.
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
What are functions/mixins?
This are used in preprocessors , its very similar to a function in javascript which returns single
value of any SASS data property.
